178.7	Kerala	Kerala	The state has an area of 38,863 km2 (15,005 sq mi) and is bordered by Karnataka to the north and northeast, Tamil Nadu to the east and south, and the Arabian Sea on the west. Thiruvananthapuram is the state capital. Kochi and Kozhikode are other major cities. According to a survey by The Economic Times, five out of ten best cities to live in India are located in Kerala. Kerala is a popular destination for its backwaters, beaches, Ayurvedic tourism and tropical greenery.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/c/c6/A_typical_houseboat_in_the_Kerala_backwaters_near_Alleppey.jpg/250px-A_typical_houseboat_in_the_Kerala_backwaters_near_Alleppey.jpg
